1. Nature of the Service

ComponentBox is an e-commerce platform specialized in high-performance computer hardware. By using our site, you guarantee that you have the legal capacity to purchase electronic components and that you understand the risks associated with handling sensitive hardware.

2. Prices and Market Volatility

Due to the nature of the semiconductor market, the prices of graphics cards (GPUs) and RAM memory may fluctuate daily. ComponentBox guarantees the product price only at the moment of payment confirmation. No refunds will be made for price differences if the product decreases in value after purchase.

3. Responsibility in Assembly

If you purchase individual components for your own assembly:

  • ComponentBox is not responsible for damage caused by electrostatic discharge (ESD).
  • Improper handling of pins in the motherboard socket (bent pins) immediately voids the factory warranty.
  • The use of generic or low-quality power supplies (PSUs) with high-end components is the sole responsibility of the user.

4. Limitation of Liability

In no event shall ComponentBox be liable for indirect damages, data loss, or loss of profits resulting from the failure of a hardware component. Our liability is limited exclusively to the repair or replacement of the defective component under the terms of the manufacturer’s warranty.
